// TEST: stdlib_error_output_smoke
// EXPECT: output "boom"
//
// A `main` that constructs an error via `core.error.error(...)` and prints its
// message. This fixture lives under `stdlib/` (directive-harness scope: loaded,
// not cross-target executed). The cross-target *execution* of `core.error`
// `.message()` is covered by `conformance/exec/exec_core_error.bock`, which
// runs on rust + go (the Q-go-error-message fix locked there). The js/ts/python
// equivalents are a pre-existing field/method-name collision (see that fixture's
// header) tracked separately. This fixture is also validated by the CLI-level
// `bock run` smoke test in bock-cli's `stdlib_error` integration suite against
// the interpreter.
module main

use core.error.{error}

public fn main() {
  println(error("boom").message())
}
